11#include <arm_neon.h>
12#include <assert.h>
13
14#include "./vp9_rtcd.h"
15
16int64_t vp9_block_error_fp_neon(const int16_t *coeff, const int16_t *dqcoeff,
17 int block_size) {
18 int64x2_t error = vdupq_n_s64(0);
19
20 assert(block_size >= 8);
21 assert((block_size % 8) == 0);
22
23 do {
24 const int16x8_t c = vld1q_s16(coeff);
25 const int16x8_t d = vld1q_s16(dqcoeff);
26 const int16x8_t diff = vsubq_s16(c, d);
27 const int16x4_t diff_lo = vget_low_s16(diff);
28 const int16x4_t diff_hi = vget_high_s16(diff);
29 // diff is 15-bits, the squares 30, so we can store 2 in 31-bits before
30 // accumulating them in 64-bits.
31 const int32x4_t err0 = vmull_s16(diff_lo, diff_lo);
32 const int32x4_t err1 = vmlal_s16(err0, diff_hi, diff_hi);
33 const int64x2_t err2 = vaddl_s32(vget_low_s32(err1), vget_high_s32(err1));
34 error = vaddq_s64(error, err2);
35 coeff += 8;
36 dqcoeff += 8;
37 block_size -= 8;
38 } while (block_size != 0);
39
40 return vgetq_lane_s64(error, 0) + vgetq_lane_s64(error, 1);
41}
